## 6. UK COMPANY — DORMANCY VS DISSOLUTION

### Recommendation: File for DORMANCY (Not Dissolution)

| Factor | Dormancy | Dissolution |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| Cost | £13/year (filing fee) | £10 one-time (DS01 form) |
| Time | 5 minutes to file | 3-4 months (Gazette publication + objection period) |
| Reversibility | Fully reversible | Irreversible (company deleted) |
| Company name | Preserved ("Trip Tailors Travel Ltd") | Released (anyone can register it) |
| Future use | Can reactivate for UK operations | Must incorporate fresh |
| Risk | None | Lose name and company number |

**Why dormancy is better:**
1. The name "Trip Tailors Travel Ltd" is your registered brand — don't lose it
2. UK-based agents or investors may prefer dealing with a UK entity
3. Future UK expansion becomes trivial (just reactivate)
4. Cost is negligible (£13/year)
5. No filing complexity (just dormant accounts annually)

**How to file dormant accounts:**
1. File AA02 (Confirmation Statement) annually: £13 via Companies House
2. File dormant accounts (balance sheet only, no P&L): free to file
3. Inform HMRC the company is dormant (letter or online)
4. No corporation tax return needed while dormant
5. Cancel any VAT registration
6. Close UK bank account (or maintain with minimal balance)

**Timeline:** File for dormancy AFTER Dubai entity is operational and all contracts transferred.

